Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:32.82,Dialogue Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,you're in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.28,0:01:44.95,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,West Izu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.92,0:01:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inspector insisted we try his car, so we borrowed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:01:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What good luck we have, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.64,0:02:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With Uncle involved, it may have actually gone like...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.56,0:02:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, because of that, may I please\Nuse it, Inspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.19,0:02:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I beg you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.69,0:02:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose not, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.28,0:02:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Inspector Megure-dono!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.79,0:02:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fairly certain you pressured him\Ninto letting you borrow the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.79,0:02:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you call us lucky...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.38,0:02:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with all this rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.22,0:02:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't see Mount Fuji at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:42.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.39,0:02:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.76,0:02:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back on the subject, Dad, how much\Nlonger until we get to that house?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.68,0:02:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not sure, but I think we'll be there shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.23,0:03:02.95,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,THE GUNSHOT AT THE SUNFLOWER ESTATE
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.45,0:03:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took us a while to arrive since\Nwe couldn't see the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and the rain has also stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.13,0:03:14.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.88,0:03:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.88,0:03:20.42,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Kanazawa Ryuuichirou (32)\NArchitect
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.13,0:03:18.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We were waiting for you to arrive, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.21,0:03:22.89,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I always read about your famous\Ndeductions in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too, I've read about you in the newspapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're that gifted architect Kanazawa\NRyuuichirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.97,0:03:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard they gave you a new prize not too long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.73,0:03:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me think, what was the name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.65,0:03:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shanghai modern art museum\Ninternational competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.90,0:03:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, are these your guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I present to you, Hayashida and Amamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.86,0:03:44.91,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Hayashida Makoto (26)\NKanazawa Architecture Office Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.36,0:03:44.91,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hi, I'm Hayashida Makoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.70,0:03:47.62,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Amamori Masaya (25)\NKanazawa Architecture Office Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.03,0:03:47.62,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And I'm Amamori Masaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just listen and be surprised, this is Mouri Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.37,0:03:54.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.38,0:03:59.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am the famous detective, Mouri Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.05,0:04:03.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've gotta stop referring to\N{\i1}yourself{\i0} as a famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stalker?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.22,0:04:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.26,0:04:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been getting these pictures every\Nweek since three months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems you appear in all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.78,0:04:23.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, we have to uncover this person's particulars;\Ndo you have any idea who it might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.41,0:04:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, think hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.78,0:04:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The voice of experience tells me that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a high probability that the stalker\Nis someone you know very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.67,0:04:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like for example...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.63,0:04:40.96,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,7:00 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.84,0:04:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The delivery is tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.30,0:04:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place is a hotel in Shanghai.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shanghai?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.10,0:04:49.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, our job is to stand guard over the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.27,0:04:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Amamori?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.98,0:04:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, by the way, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what\Ndo you think of this building?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.02,0:05:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This building has a strange aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.94,0:05:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:06.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master designed it himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.70,0:05:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite pretty, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:09.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.95,0:05:12.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It felt like the structure itself was moving...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true that it has moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second floor does a revolution\Nover the course of 12 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.92,0:05:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we call it the sunflower estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.09,0:05:23.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:26.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did the master build a moving house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.64,0:05:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll ask the master next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.22,0:05:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.77,0:05:39.90,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Kanazawa Mitsuko (38)\NKanazawa's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:37.14,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,His architecture is random.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.14,0:05:38.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's just lying to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.90,0:05:42.44,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,7:10 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.69,0:05:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am sure everything will be solved\Naround the time you get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.70,0:05:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope that will be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.28,0:05:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, if possible, could you do me a favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.62,0:05:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This man!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.83,0:06:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you do an investigation\Non the honesty of this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.63,0:06:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the remuneration is greatly split,\NI may have half the compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuko, can't you stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.47,0:06:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you be able to take the plane\Ntomorrow being drunk like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you go to the ceremony alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.27,0:06:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or are you going there with your stalker?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.31,0:06:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you to stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.44,0:06:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems it's you who has to drop this act.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.36,0:06:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You give the impression you're really\Nworried about that stalker, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.07,0:06:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In reality, you just got what you deserve, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From a woman you dumped before or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.99,0:06:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hayashida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.50,0:06:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you've been eating till now is meat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but this meat...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.13,0:06:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meat, meat... with those unbalanced eating habits...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.92,0:06:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll never be able to taste originality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:52.72,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,7:20 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.51,0:06:52.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're in the middle of a conversation here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.05,0:06:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.30,0:06:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get beer from the fridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.31,0:07:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Darling, if you keep persecuting these weaklings...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.19,0:07:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll finally pull out these pet dogs' fangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Amamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:17.54,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,7:25 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get a bit more coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.53,0:07:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you watch the food so it doesn't get burned?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.50,0:07:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this dressing tastes good with salad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:29.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it says "olive oil" there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.26,0:07:31.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, apologies!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a very special dressing that I made,\Nbut I didn't have another bottle to put it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.76,0:07:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be forced to taste it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:42.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her taste is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, isn't it your taste that's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.53,0:07:50.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 7:29 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.24,0:07:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One minute left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.32,0:07:52.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.82,0:07:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.16,0:08:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Amamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, where did Kanazawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.17,0:08:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To see the Chinese lesson broadcast on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.75,0:08:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's very eager to do his speech in\NChinese at the award ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.51,0:08:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how busy he is nowadays,\Nhe always watches it live.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a foolish hobby?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:27.40,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,7:35 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.78,0:08:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, my beer was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.87,0:08:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you need some, here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How kind of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, haven't you had enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying, it's normal that I drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.76,0:08:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.31,0:09:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.07,0:09:12.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door's locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.36,0:09:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any spare keys?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.86,0:09:14.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.11,0:09:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have no choice but to break down the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.41,0:09:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go get an axe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.66,0:09:21.37,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,7:40 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.83,0:09:27.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.46,0:09:30.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.71,0:09:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.55,0:09:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.88,0:09:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, turn on the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.26,0:09:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.72,0:09:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:42.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was known architect\NKanazawa Ryuuichirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.16,0:10:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Kanazawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} always\Nsat here when he watched TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:11.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He died instantly from a bullet to the head, and\Nthe weapon has yet to be found in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.37,0:10:10.79,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo\NShizuoka Prefectural Police
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.88,0:10:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beyond that, the windows are\Nall locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, this is a sealed room murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.59,0:10:23.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there's a mark indicating that\Nthe bullet penetrated here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the place from where the culprit shot is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.93,0:10:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place is? The place is where?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.77,0:10:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.94,0:10:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please stop it with the jokes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.11,0:10:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, say, isn't it so great?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.24,0:10:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way this room revolves over 12 hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Revolves?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.66,0:10:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now it's 8:35...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.33,0:10:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you say you heard the shot an hour ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.09,0:10:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we draw a line between the victim's\Nposition and the hole in the window glass...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.76,0:11:00.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with one hour meaning 30 degrees, we get to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.76,0:11:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.19,0:11:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.81,0:11:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the decoration on the side of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be oil, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.78,0:11:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.95,0:11:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.41,0:11:28.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we haven't found any footprints\Naround the pine tree where the rifle was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.12,0:11:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we did find some around in\Nthe yard and the party area.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.62,0:11:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From around 6:00 to 6:30 this afternoon, it\Nwas raining pretty heavily around this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.09,0:11:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which basically means no one got near the tree\Nwhere the weapon was found after 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, how the hell did the sniper shoot?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.48,0:11:54.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the time being, please look\Nfor the owner of this rifle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.02,0:11:54.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.86,0:11:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.77,0:12:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This rifle is damp, so I guess the killer must\Nhave placed it here before it rained.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.20,0:12:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The target is perfectly locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.20,0:12:08.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the weapon we were looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.24,0:12:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where did the killer disappear\Nto after he pulled the trigger?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you think the\Nkiller jumped into the water!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.75,0:12:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there's a beach directly below.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.96,0:12:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to jump right into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.51,0:12:23.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.01,0:12:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a fishing line...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The end of the line is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.19,0:12:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wire's covered in mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.23,0:12:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's also mud on the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A heavy load...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.15,0:12:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I understand everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.49,0:12:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It happened like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.70,0:12:52.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit knew precisely when the victim watched\NTV and calculated when the bullet should be shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.95,0:12:57.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the crime, they pulled the\Nstring and the heavy load from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.96,0:13:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doing so, they never had to enter the villa and\Nmeant to lead us to believe they've escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.01,0:13:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying the culprit is from the outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we are dealing with someone\Nthat knows the victim's routine well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.26,0:13:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.81,0:13:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim recently began receiving\Nvicious threats from a stalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.56,0:13:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the stalker is the one responsible!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.90,0:13:22.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe that to be the most reasonable conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.07,0:13:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That much is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.28,0:13:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's amazing Uncle hasn't made a mistake yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.49,0:13:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible for anyone at the party to have\Npulled the trigger when the shot was fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did they disguise the crime\Nin such a complicated manner?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.54,0:13:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.42,0:13:42.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was mud on the wire and the rifle...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.01,0:13:46.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rain in the evening should have cleaned it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.88,0:13:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.55,0:13:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it have been done to hide something?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.14,0:13:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.43,0:13:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.94,0:13:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rifle was the property of the deceased.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.19,0:14:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The robbery was reported by\Nthe owner himself last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.48,0:14:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.53,0:14:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the substance on the decoration outside\Nthe second floor turned out to be oil after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:13.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, please allow me to review\Nthe events of today for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.34,0:14:24.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after his arrival at 6:45...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.01,0:14:29.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went up to the second floor with Kanazawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.59,0:14:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Hayashida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand Amamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were in the backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.35,0:14:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you, Miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.81,0:14:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was drinking a little brandy in the kitchen\Nand I got out of there just after 7:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:50.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The party started at 7:10 when\NMouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kanazawa came down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.45,0:14:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And at 7:20, Hayashida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}: You\Nwent to the kitchen for beers?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.95,0:14:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were absent for approximately 5 minutes, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:14:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} changed roles with you\Nwhen he left to retrieve some coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.17,0:15:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was gone for 4 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.88,0:15:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 7:29, Kanazawa went up alone to his\Nlibrary on the second floor to watch TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward, I came out to go to the bathroom at 7:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.48,0:15:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard the gunshot when I returned 5 minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.94,0:15:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to confirm one more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:26.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the gunshot...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the guests were actually at the party, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.65,0:15:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.57,0:15:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why none of us could have pulled the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.33,0:15:42.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know what the trick was, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:44.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.92,0:15:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.59,0:15:50.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mr. Policemen, there's\Nsomething on the ground here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.80,0:15:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.34,0:15:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, Uncle Mouri asked me to\Nhave you guys check a few things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.56,0:16:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The diameter of the building is 20 meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.06,0:16:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the distance from the tree where\Nwe found the rifle is about 10 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.48,0:16:12.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The length of the fishing line that was secured to\Nthe rifle is exactly 10 meters and 2 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.53,0:16:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.95,0:16:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.08,0:16:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.66,0:16:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.87,0:16:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where the hell has he gone off to this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.01,0:16:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is no time to sleep, help me find Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.30,0:16:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.05,0:16:39.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.22,0:16:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.35,0:16:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I also found out who the murderer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.31,0:16:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, could you tell everyone to gather here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.65,0:16:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.90,0:16:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you told us a moment ago the\Nkiller can't be someone from the house!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:16:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget all that I told you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.49,0:17:04.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it's true that if you pull on the wire\Nfrom over the cliff, it will pull the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.04,0:17:09.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was to deceive us into believing the\Ncrime had been committed by an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.59,0:17:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the culprit didn't notice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.17,0:17:17.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That traces of mud had stuck\Nonto the trigger and the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.30,0:17:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it rained, the mud should have been washed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.27,0:17:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the shooting\Noccurred in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the person capable of the crime is\Nright here amongst us as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.70,0:17:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to reveal, right here and now, how the bullet\Nwas shot without anyone pulling the trigger directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.91,0:17:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.62,0:17:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind giving me a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.67,0:17:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please roll that hardened paper up and\Nform a pipe with double-sided tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.71,0:17:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then turn it into a pole...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.63,0:17:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And put tape around the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.09,0:18:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this double-sided tape you're talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.14,0:18:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, I found this on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.23,0:18:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, this belongs to the culprit!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.27,0:18:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When everything is ready,\Nplease take a look at the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.15,0:18:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was found next to the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please attach it to the end of the pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.70,0:18:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then pick it up pointing at the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.37,0:18:32.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fishing wire on the pine tree sticks, and\Nthen, the heavy load on the other end...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.21,0:18:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.46,0:18:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there was mud on the wire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.17,0:18:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now look at the top of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.38,0:18:39.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See anything in particular?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.26,0:18:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the top?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The decoration on the 2nd floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.89,0:18:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.52,0:18:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit hooked the fishing wire there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.06,0:18:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weight was gradually lifted...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally it pulled the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.07,0:19:01.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, the killer had been very careful...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.07,0:19:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By putting oil on the decoration in order to\Nensure the wire would continue sliding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.95,0:19:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he put a tissue soaked with oil on the\Nend newspaper pole and spread some oil...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.33,0:19:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the wire and the trigger beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.88,0:19:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In all, it would have taken the culprit\None minute to carry it all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.93,0:19:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.55,0:19:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer, who is it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.97,0:19:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it's you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.31,0:19:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 7:25, you left the backyard saying\Nyou were going for a bit of coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.58,0:19:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had already prepared the fishing\Nline and pole you'd hid beforehand...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And carried out your trick before\Ninnocently going back to the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.80,0:20:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You employed the newspaper sheets\Nused for the stick to carry the coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.26,0:20:09.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging by the length of the wire, the wire\Nremained hooked up for 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, we heard the gunshot at 7:35...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.52,0:20:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the culprit left the party during\Nthe 10 minute time frame from 7:25.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:23.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are the only one that could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.95,0:20:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of you knew the real Kanazawa\NRyuuichirou, I'm certain of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.08,0:20:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who designed the Shanghai\NMuseum of Modern Art was me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.96,0:20:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying I stole your design?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.26,0:20:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.38,0:20:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.09,0:20:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have always respected you, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:20:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will say only this:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You do not realize your current position.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.81,0:20:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This design has won the eye of the\Npublic thanks to me and my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.90,0:21:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to stay here, be very\Ncareful about what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.32,0:21:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that moment, I swore to myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I wouldn't allow him to attend the prize ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.00,0:21:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the stalker that corresponded with him was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.38,0:21:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.51,0:21:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I created an imaginary stalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.63,0:21:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything was going as I planned, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.01,0:21:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything but you appearing here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.03,0:21:48.49,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Always
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.03,0:21:48.49,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Song By Mai Kuraki
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.25,0:21:56.08,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.54,0:21:59.13,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love to you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.46,0:22:01.29,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.75,0:22:04.34,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love to you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.51,0:22:12.51,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,son janai ima kara de mo iin janai yareru koto
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.51,0:22:12.51,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,It's not a big thing! From now on there won't be any problems! We can make it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.64,0:22:23.23,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,omotta doori ni yatte miyou kimi to deau made
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.64,0:22:23.23,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Let's give it a go. Like we wanted to, until I met you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.73,0:22:29.91,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,nani mo nakatta keredo me o tojite omou
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.73,0:22:29.91,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,I had nothing, but I closed my eyes and I could believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.03,0:22:34.58,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,issho ni ikiru basho ga aru kara
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.03,0:22:34.58,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Because there is a place, where you and I always can be together
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.87,0:22:41.13,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,always ai no mune ni yuuki o dashite
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.87,0:22:41.13,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Always have courage and love, in your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.38,0:22:45.76,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,tatoe sore ga dame da to shite mo ne
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.38,0:22:45.76,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Even if you think it's no use
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.88,0:22:51.14,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,No sore dake ga jibun janai
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.88,0:22:51.14,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,No, that's just not like me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.26,0:22:56.68,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Yes kazamuki ga kawatta ima tobitatou
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.26,0:22:56.68,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Yes, now that the direction of the wind has changed, let's fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.81,0:22:58.56,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.06,0:23:01.69,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.40,0:23:02.52,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.98,0:23:09.32,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my, give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.37,0:23:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.50,0:23:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I will ever be able to trust people\Nthat are self-proclaimed geniuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.29,0:23:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you don't trust me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.30,0:23:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imagine that the great Mouri Kogoro\Nis not the one solving all these cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.30,0:23:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think of that idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.40,0:23:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a great guess!
